## Biography

Jeff Bezos founded Amazon in 1994 as an online bookstore from a garage in Seattle. With relentless customer focus and long-term vision, he expanded into retail, cloud computing (AWS), streaming, and entertainment. Despite Wall Street pressure, he maintained Day 1 mentality—reinvesting profits and optimizing for customer joy over near-term earnings. His principle 'Your margin is my opportunity' disrupted entire industries. AWS transformed cloud computing while generating majority profits. He step...

